@* Demonstrates child-to-parent communication via an explicit, manually-wired EventCallback,
   without @bind-Value sugar. The parent passes Value down as a one-way parameter and supplies
   an OnValueChanged handler that writes the new string back to its own field. Contrast with
   NameInput.razor, which achieves the same underlying mechanism using @bind-Value shorthand
   (Blazor desugars @bind-Value into exactly Value + ValueChanged). Holds no state of its own.
   The parameter is named OnValueChanged (not ValueChanged) deliberately, so the @bind-Value
   shorthand cannot be used and callers must wire it explicitly. *@

<textarea class="form-control"
          rows="4"
          placeholder="Describe the order"
          @onchange="@(async e => await OnValueChanged.InvokeAsync(e.Value?.ToString() ?? string.Empty))">@Value</textarea>

@code {
    /// <summary>Current value supplied by the parent.</summary>
    [Parameter] public string Value { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    /// <summary>
    /// Callback invoked when the user changes the textarea. Named OnValueChanged (not
    /// ValueChanged) so Blazor's @bind-Value shorthand cannot be used — callers must wire
    /// this explicitly.
    /// </summary>
    [Parameter] public EventCallback<string> OnValueChanged { get; set; }
}
